=== cmd 0: [fork --help] ===
Manage network fork mode

Fork mode lets you test deployment scripts against local forks of live networks with snapshot/revert
workflow.

Usage: treb fork [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  enter    Enter fork mode: snapshot registry and start Anvil for all configured networks
  exit     Exit fork mode: stop all Anvils, restore registry from snapshot
  revert   Revert all forks to their initial state
  restart  Restart the fork from a new block
  status   Show active fork status
  history  Show fork history
  diff     Diff current registry vs snapshot
  logs     Tail Anvil log files for active forks
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also respected via NO_COLOR env var)

      --non-interactive
          Skip interactive prompts (also enabled via TREB_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, CI=true, or non-TTY
          stdin/stdout)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Use "treb fork [command] --help" for more information about a command.
